Images follow the following convention:

[identifier]-[name]-[aspect-ratio]-[additional-tags].[extension]

examples:
    athlon-logo-500x500.webp
    athlon-logo-500x500-nobg.webp
    athlon-logo-inverse-500x500-nobg.webp

additional tags:
note: tags are indicated by either a dash ( - ) or a period ( . )

    -nobg --> indicates that the asset does not have a background
    -v{iteration}  --> indicates the asset version. only the newest versions are used.

note: vectors do not follow this naming convention.